      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 rounded-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h2 id="intro" class="h4">Introduction</h2>
            <p>
              Thank you for choosing
              <strong>Online Academy</strong>. We respect your privacy and want
              you to understand how we collect, use, and share information about
              you. This policy also explains your rights regarding your personal
              data.
            </p>

            <h2 id="scope" class="h4 mt-4">Scope</h2>
            <p>
              Unless we link to a different policy, this Privacy Policy applies
              when you visit or use Online Academy websites, mobile apps, APIs,
              and related services (the “Services”). By using the Services, you
              agree to this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree, please do not
              use the Services.
            </p>

            <h2 id="data-we-get" class="h4 mt-4">1. What Data We Collect</h2>
            <p>We collect data you provide directly and data collected
              automatically when you use the Services.</p>
            <div class="accordion" id="accData">
              <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="acc1h1">
                  <button
                    class="accordion-button collapsed"
                    type="button"
                    data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                    data-bs-target="#acc1c1"
                  >1.1 Data You Provide</button>
                </h2>
                <div
                  id="acc1c1"
                  class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                  data-bs-parent="#accData"
                >
                  <div class="accordion-body">
                    <ul>
                      <li><strong>Account Data:</strong>
                        email, password, settings, optional phone for 2FA.</li>
                      <li><strong>Profile Data:</strong>
                        name, photo, headline, bio, links, country (publicly
                        viewable).</li>
                      <li><strong>Shared Content:</strong>
                        reviews, Q&A, posts, course uploads (public as
                        configured).</li>
                      <li><strong>Learning Data:</strong>
                        enrolled courses, progress, certificates, quizzes,
                        submissions.</li>
                      <li><strong>Payment Data (Students):</strong>
                        billing name/address; card data handled by payment
                        providers (we don’t store full card numbers).</li>
                      <li><strong>Payment Data (Instructors):</strong>
                        payout account info (e.g., PayPal/Payoneer), tax info as
                        required by law.</li>
                      <li><strong>Connected Accounts:</strong>
                        info we receive if you log in via third-party platforms
                        (depends on your settings there).</li>
                      <li><strong>Promotions & Surveys:</strong>
                        info you submit to participate (name, contact details,
                        responses).</li>
                      <li><strong>Support:</strong>
                        messages and contact details when you reach out to us.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="mb-0 small text-muted">Legal bases include
                      performance of contract, legitimate interests (service
                      provisioning, security, fraud prevention, communications),
                      and legal obligations.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="acc1h2">
                  <button
                    class="accordion-button collapsed"
                    type="button"
                    data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                    data-bs-target="#acc1c2"
                  >1.2 Data Collected Automatically</button>
                </h2>
                <div
                  id="acc1c2"
                  class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                  data-bs-parent="#accData"
                >
                  <div class="accordion-body">
                    <ul>
                      <li><strong>System Data:</strong>
                        IP, device, OS, browser, language, identifiers.</li>
                      <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong>
                        pages visited, time spent, features used, search
                        queries, clicks.</li>
                      <li><strong>Approx. Location:</strong>
                        city/country inferred from IP.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="mb-0 small text-muted">Collected via cookies,
                      logs, and similar technologies (see Section 2).</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="acc1h3">
                  <button
                    class="accordion-button collapsed"
                    type="button"
                    data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                    data-bs-target="#acc1c3"
                  >1.3 Data From Third Parties</button>
                </h2>
                <div
                  id="acc1c3"
                  class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                  data-bs-parent="#accData"
                >
                  <div class="accordion-body">
                    <p>For business customers/prospects, we may receive business
                      contact information from reputable providers for outreach
                      and service delivery.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <h2 id="how-we-get" class="h4 mt-4">2. How We Collect It</h2>
            <p>We use cookies, web beacons, tags, and similar tools. You can
              manage preferences in your browser and (where available) in our
              cookie banner.</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Strictly Necessary:</strong>
                enable core functionality and security.</li>
              <li><strong>Functional:</strong>
                remember preferences and enhance experience.</li>
              <li><strong>Performance:</strong> analytics and A/B testing.</li>
              <li><strong>Advertising & Social:</strong>
                deliver and measure ads; enable social features.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="use-of-data" class="h4 mt-4">3. How We Use It</h2>
            <p>We use your data to provide and improve the Services, process
              orders and payouts, communicate with you, secure our platform,
              personalize content/ads (where permitted), comply with law, and
              for safety and integrity. We retain data only as long as needed
              for these purposes or as required by law.</p>

            <h2 id="sharing" class="h4 mt-4">4. Who We Share With</h2>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Instructors & Students:</strong>
                limited info related to courses you access; shared content and
                profiles may be public per your settings.</li>
              <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong>
                payments, analytics, hosting, support, marketing—bound by
                contract to protect data.</li>
              <li><strong>Affiliates & Partners:</strong>
                to operate and distribute the Services.</li>
              <li><strong>Compliance & Safety:</strong>
                to meet legal requests, enforce terms, prevent fraud, and
                protect rights.</li>
              <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong>
                in case of merger, acquisition, or asset sale.</li>
              <li><strong>Aggregated/De-identified Data:</strong>
                may be used for any purpose.</li>
              <li><strong>With Your Consent:</strong>
                as additionally agreed by you.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="security" class="h4 mt-4">5. Security</h2>
            <p>We apply appropriate technical and organizational measures based
              on data sensitivity. No online service can be 100% secure. Protect
              your password and contact us if you suspect unauthorized access.</p>

            <h2 id="your-rights" class="h4 mt-4">6. Your Rights & Choices</h2>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Communications:</strong>
                opt out of promo emails via the unsubscribe link; we’ll still
                send transactional messages.</li>
              <li><strong>Cookies:</strong>
                manage via browser settings and our cookie controls (where
                available).</li>
              <li><strong>Access/Update/Delete:</strong>
                manage in your account settings or contact us (see Section 8).</li>
              <li><strong>Children:</strong>
                users under the age required for online consent may not use the
                Services; parents can request deletion of a child’s data.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="jurisdictions" class="h4 mt-4">7. Jurisdiction-Specific
              Rules</h2>
            <p>Depending on where you live, you may have additional rights
              (e.g., California, EEA/UK, Australia). We honor valid requests
              under applicable law, including access, correction, deletion,
              restriction/objection, portability, and opt-out of certain
              processing (like targeted ads).</p>
            <p class="small text-muted mb-0">Transfers outside your region are
              protected using appropriate safeguards (e.g., standard contractual
              clauses) and service-provider contracts.</p>

            <h2 id="updates-contact" class="h4 mt-4">8. Updates & Contact</h2>
            <p>We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes
              will be notified via email or in-product notice. Continued use
              after the effective date means you accept the revised policy.</p>
